1. The Global Entry Point
    main.jsx: This is the very first file configured to render the entire application. It wraps the App component with BrowserRouter for navigation and ShopContextProvider to provide global data like product lists and currency.

    App.jsx: Located in the src folder, this acts as the "Master Layout". It contains the Navbar, all defined Routes, and the Footer, ensuring these elements appear on every page.

2. The Core Page Development Flow
    The pages in your src/pages/ folder were generally created in this order:

    Home.jsx: The landing page. It was built by assembling the Hero section and the LatestCollections component to show featured products.

    Collection.jsx: Created next to allow users to view all products. This page handles complex logic like category filtering and price sorting.

    Product.jsx: Developed to show detailed information for a single item. It allows users to view different images, read descriptions, and select sizes.

    Cart.jsx: Built once the "Add to Cart" logic was established in the context. It displays a summary of selected items and calculates the total.

    Placeorder.jsx: The checkout form where users enter delivery information and select a payment method.

    Orders.jsx: A final user-facing page that displays a history of successful purchases.

    About.jsx & Contact.jsx: These were typically created last as they are mostly static informational pages.

    Login.jsx: Added to handle user authentication (Login/Sign Up).

1. src/context/
Files: ShopContext.jsx

Purpose: This folder contains the "Global State" of your app. It manages information that every page needs access to, such as your product list, the shopping cart items, and settings like the currency symbol or delivery fees.

2. src/components/
Files: Hero.jsx, Navbar.jsx, Title.jsx, ProductItem.jsx, Footer.jsx, NewsletterBox.jsx, OurPolicy.jsx, SearchBar.jsx, CartTotal.jsx

Purpose: This folder is for reusable UI blocks. These are small pieces of the website that appear on multiple pages. For example, the Navbar and Footer appear on every page, while ProductItem is reused whenever a product needs to be displayed in a list.

3. src/pages/
Files: Home.jsx, Collection.jsx, About.jsx, Contact.jsx, Product.jsx, Cart.jsx, Login.jsx, PlaceOrder.jsx, Orders.jsx

Purpose: This folder contains the full-screen views. Each file here represents a specific destination or "Route" that a user visits (e.g., the /cart page or the /about page). These pages are built by combining the smaller components from the components folder.

4. src/ (Root folder)
Files: App.jsx, main.jsx, index.css

Purpose: This is the foundation of the application. main.jsx starts the app and connects it to the HTML. App.jsx handles the routing logic (deciding which page to show based on the URL). index.css contains your global styles and font imports.